===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Dana had a population of 38, with 12 households and 8 families residing in the city.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A18345&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 135.4 inhabitants per square mile (52.3/km<sup>2</sup>), and there were 24 housing units at an average density of 85.5 per square mile (33.0/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A18345&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

The median age in the city was 36.5 years. 23.7% of residents were under the age of 18 and 15.8% were 65 years of age or older. Age distribution was 23.7% under the age of 20, 5.3% from 20 to 24, 28.9% from 25 to 44, 26.3% from 45 to 64, and 15.8% age 65 or older. For every 100 females there were 90.0 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 123.1 males age 18 and over. The gender makeup of the city was 47.4% male and 52.6% female.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A18345&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 12 households, 33.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them. Of all households, 50.0% were married-couple households, 8.3% were cohabitating-couple households, 41.7% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present, and 0.0% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present. 33.3% of households were non-families. About 25.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 0.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 24 housing units, of which 50.0% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 50.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

